  "suggestion": "Efficiency bottleneck: organisms thrash in place. Diversity bottleneck: no behavioral niche specialization. Solve both by reducing baseline metabolic cost (energyConserve, low moveSpeed) and creating trade-offs (aggressive harvesting vs. exploration).; Efficiency is critically weak (0.409 vs survivalRate 0.833). This dominates the limiting factor — organisms spend too much energy moving/pulsing relative to resources harvested. Also, diversityOfForms (0.457) is low because all organisms converge on similar strategies. Fix by: (1) lowering moveSpeed and increasing energyConserve globally to reduce waste, (2) increasing harvestThreshold so organisms stop wasting energy on poor-value resources, (3) spreading organisms with avoidanceRadius to reduce crowding and improve spatial composition (0.3), (4) introducing phenotypic divergence — some ultra-conservative (metabolically cheap), others aggressive resource hunters.",
